-- 
Aegis, BBVA, Lufthansa, ING Groep: European Equity Preview

-- B y   C e c i l e   V a n n u c c i
-- 
2011-03-17T04:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/aegis-banco-espirito-bbva-lufthansa-ing-europe-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index fell 1.6 percent to 262.18. The
Stoxx 50 Index dropped 1.7 percent to 2,466.49. The Euro Stoxx
50 Index, a benchmark for nations using the euro, declined 2.3
percent to 2,721.24.    Aegis Group Plc (AGS)  : The world’s largest independent
buyer of advertising space may report full-year net income of 83
million pounds ($133 million) according to the average of seven
estimates compiled by Bloomberg. The stock declined 0.8 percent
to 130.4 pence.    Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)  :  Spain ’s
second largest bank said in a filing its scrip dividend program
would be implemented in April with shareholders having until
April 11 to say if they want to be remunerated in cash. The
shares lost 4 percent to 8.54 euros.    Banco Espirito Santo SA (BES)  ,  Banco Comercial Portugues
SA (BCP)  :  Portugal ’s biggest banks may be active after the  Finance Ministry  said it does not foresee a need to increase
banks’ capital with government funds. Espirito Santo shares lost
2.6 percent to 3.14 euros. BCP shares slipped 1.3 percent to
63.4 euro cents.    Deutsche Lufthansa AG (LHA)  : The German carrier said it
will order 30 of Airbus SAS’ new A320neo-series planes for about
$2.8 billion at list price as well as five Boeing Co. 777 cargo
planes worth $1.35 billion. It fell 3 percent to 13.57 euros.    EnBW Energie Baden-Wuerttemberg AG (EBK)  :  Germany ’s
third-largest utility is seeking a 2 billion-euro ($2.8 billion)
facility to replace an existing credit line, a person familiar
with the deal said. EnBW shares were unchanged at 41.31 euros.  Fluxys SA (FLUX BB): The manager of  Belgium ’s natural-gas
grid will pay a final dividend of 220 euros a share and said it
plans to maintain the distribution next year, not taking into
account the extraordinary interim dividend of 228 euros a share
in December 2010.  Fluxys (FLUX)  retreated 0.1 percent to 2,310 euros.    ING Groep NV (INGA)  ,  SNS Reaal NV (SR)  : Dutch banks
will have to pay about 400 million euros annually to create a
deposit-guarantee fund, Finance Minister  Jan Kees de Jager  said.
Banks will pay a premium equal to 0.1 percent of their deposits,
starting in July 2012, De Jager said. ING, the biggest Dutch
financial-services company, declined 2.4 percent to 8.39 euros.
SNS dropped 0.3 percent to 3.62 euros.  K+S AG (SDF GY): Europe’s biggest potash producer said
Capital Research and Management Co.’s voting rights in the
company exceeded the 3 percent level requiring regulatory
disclosure and amounted to 3.13 percent on March 11. Shares of
K+S advanced 0.6 percent to 49.32 euros.    Legal & General Group Plc (LGEN)  : The U.K.’s fourth-
biggest insurer may report full-year net income of 873.3 million
pounds, according to the average of seven estimates compiled by
Bloomberg. The shares fell 0.7 percent to 111.1 pence.    Premier Farnell Plc (PFL)  : The U.K. supplier of
electronic components may report full-year net income of 65.3
million pounds, according to the average of five estimates
compiled by Bloomberg. The shares dropped 1.3 percent to 276.6
pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
